        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 24 at 6:48PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 646 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Pear Valley, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brady, San Saba, Richland Springs, Algerita, Cherokee, Melvin, Brady
Lake, Sloan, Lohn, Waldrip, Calf Creek, Skeeterville, Voca, Chappel,
Elm Grove, Winchell, Camp San Saba, Rochelle, Pear Valley, and Doole.

People attending the football game at Richland Springs Coyote Field
should seek safe shelter immediately.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Very heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 PM CDT for
west central Texas. A Severe Thunderstorm Watch also remains in
effect until midnight CDT for west central Texas.</instruction>
